dllibinfo

Returns list of available symbols in an shared library.

Syntax

c = dllibinfo(lib)

Input argument

lib

a dllib handle: library already loaded.

Output argument

c

a cell of strings.

Description

dllibinfo returns list of available symbols in an shared library.

Example

lib = dlopen(modulepath('dynamic_link', 'builtin'))
c = dllibinfo(lib)

See also

dlopen.
